Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm wide chips
(no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, cook on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn the #baking tray{} halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and
fry until soft and sweet, stirring occasionally, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add the @balsamic vinegar{1%sachet} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch} and cook until
the vinegar has evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once caramelised, transfer from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Lay the @Irish chicken breasts{320%g} out on a #cutting board{}.

Place your hand flat on top and carefully slice from thick end to the thin point
until there are 2cm left (don't slice all the way through). Open it up like a
book. Repeat with the other breast(s).

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal
> due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Carefully coat the chicken with the @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste},
@pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Lay the open chicken breasts on a lined baking tray.

Bake until golden and cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the chicken has 5 mins left to cook, sprinkle over the @grated cheese{50%g}
and return to the oven to gratinate.

Pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove the chicken from the oven once cooked and fold each breast back together
so they resemble closed books.

Spread some @mayo{2%sachets} and @Ballymaloe tomato relish{1%pot} over the cut
side of each bun.

Top the base bun with caramelised onions and cheesy Cajun chicken then sandwich
closed with the top bun.

Divide burgers and chips between plates. Use any remaining mayo for dipping.